snippet.textDisplay:
Hi

A big fan of Ashley here.


When the amazon video came out, everyone seemed to be entirely outraged, but now it seems like no one even cares anymore. I assume people just left because they didn't trust Ashley anymore. I didn't leave because i'm not one to cancel someone on the spot and i also really love Ashley. I feel like I've been waiting so long for an explanation of some kind, and, at this point, i feel like it's not coming. That is sad to think about since Ashley is someone who inspired me to get into sustainable fashion. I used to shop from boohoo, urban, etc. and now my closet is completely made up from vintage clothing. Now that I think of it, Ashley has never been truly sustainable- supporting pretty little thing and urban whilst also somewhat preaching about sustainable fashion (not that she has to shop sustainable, i just find her actions and her words slightly contradicting). I don't understand how we kind of swept it under the rug and acted like nothing had happened, whilst with bigger creators, we "cancel" them relentlessly. Of course, I don't want to cancel Ashley, but i just want an explanation. Or at least some self awareness of what she did.



I also commented this on her second channel
